## STANDARD UI COMPONENTS

### Buttons
Three variants — use CSS classes or lib/design-system.js values.
Never hardcode button styles inline when a class exists.

PRIMARY — .btn-primary
- bg #4ADE80, text #0a0a0a, Space Grotesk bold 700, uppercase
- height 48px, border-radius 2px, padding 0 24px
- Use for: main CTAs, form submits, key actions

SECONDARY — .btn-secondary
- transparent bg, border rgba(74,222,128,0.3), text #4ADE80
- JetBrains Mono, height 48px, border-radius 2px
- Use for: export, secondary actions, back links as buttons

GHOST — .btn-ghost
- transparent bg, border rgba(255,255,255,0.08), text #e2e2e9
- JetBrains Mono, height 48px, border-radius 2px
- Use for: tertiary actions, Google OAuth, cancel

### Top Nav
Every authenticated page uses .scopr-nav:
- sticky top-0, z-40, blur backdrop, border-bottom rgba(255,255,255,0.06)
- LEFT: >_ Scopr wordmark — always links to /dashboard
  Use wordmark values from lib/design-system.js
- RIGHT: page-specific back link using .scopr-nav-link class
  Format: // [destination] →
  - Idea capture → // back to dashboard →
  - Questions → // save draft (special case)
  - Generating → nothing
  - Decision → // back to dashboard →
  - Launch Pack → // back to decision →
  - Export → // back to launch pack →

### Wordmark
Always: >_ Scopr where "Scop" is white, "r" is #4ADE80
>_ sits in a small dark rounded square (wordmark.icon from design-system)
Use wordmark.container, wordmark.icon, wordmark.text, wordmark.accent

### // Comment Lines
- Font: JetBrains Mono, size 0.75rem, colour #4ADE80
- Always lowercase
- Hero comment lines get a blinking █ cursor using .terminal-cursor class
- Pattern: <span className="terminal-cursor">█</span>
- Use the TerminalComment component from waitlist/page.js as reference

### Typing Effect Subheading
- Used on hero/centrepiece sections only
- Speed: 35ms per character via setInterval
- Starts on page load with 0.3-0.5s delay
- Font: Inter or Space Grotesk, text-lg, text-white/85
- No cursor after it — text types in cleanly
- Reference implementation: app/waitlist/page.js

### Form Inputs
TEXT INPUT — .input-default (or inputs.default from design-system)
- bg #0c0e13, JetBrains Mono, height 44px
- Default ring: 0 0 0 1px rgba(134,148,134,0.2)
- Focus ring: 0 0 0 1px #4ADE80 (via onFocus/onBlur handlers)
- Placeholder: rgba(255,255,255,0.35)

INPUT LABEL — .input-label
- JetBrains Mono, 10px, uppercase, tracking-widest
- Colour: rgba(255,255,255,0.45)

TEXTAREA
- bg-transparent, rounded-md, padding 16px
- Font: Inter, 0.9375rem, leading-relaxed, #e2e2e9
- Placeholder: rgba(188,202,187,0.35)
- Focus: outline-none only
- Character count: absolute bottom-right, JetBrains Mono 11px, 
  rgba(188,202,187,0.5), format {current}/{max}
- Hint text below: JetBrains Mono 11px, rgba(188,202,187,0.45)
  Shows ⚠ warning when below minimum character count

### Glass Cards (neutral — default for ALL content cards)
Class: .glass-card
- background: rgba(26, 27, 33, 0.4)
- backdrop-filter: blur(8px)
- -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px)
- border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06)
- border-radius: 4px

Use for: ALL cards, panels, content boxes, score cards, 
// scopr says banner, launch pack cards, preview panels, 
quiz cards, form containers. No exceptions.

### Stat Cards (dashboard only — NOT for content cards)
Three variants — only used for the dashboard summary stats:
- .stat-card-green — build stats
- .stat-card-amber — refine stats  
- .stat-card-neutral — total/neutral stats
These use gradient backgrounds. Do NOT use for content cards.

### Card Colour Coding (left border)
- Build → border-left: 3px solid #4ADE80 (.accent-green)
- Refine → border-left: 3px solid #EF9F27 (.accent-amber)
- Revisit → border-left: 3px solid #888780 (.accent-gray)
- Draft → border-left: 3px solid #888780 (.accent-gray)

### Score Display
- Score number: Space Grotesk or JetBrains Mono, bold, text-4xl minimum
- Colour always matches decision: build=#4ADE80, refine=#EF9F27, revisit=#888780
- Score bar: .score-bar + .score-bar-fill, height 8px
- Score bar fill colour matches decision accent

### // Scopr Says Banner
- .glass-card + border-left: 3px solid #4ADE80
- Label: // scopr says in JetBrains Mono, #4ADE80, text-xs
- Content: max-height 120px, scrollable, .scopr-says-scroll
- Shows decision_summary — fallback to first 2 sentences of full_plan

### Preview Panel (launch pack)
- .glass-card, padding p-6
- Header: // [card title] in JetBrains Mono #4ADE80
- Copy button: .btn-secondary style, top-right, small
  Shows // copy → then // copied ✓ for 2 seconds on click

### Section Labels
Class: .scopr-section-label
- JetBrains Mono, 10px, uppercase, tracking 0.2em
- Colour: rgba(188,202,187,0.5)
- Example: "YOUR LAUNCH PACK — CLICK ANY CARD TO PREVIEW"

### Badges
- .badge-v2 — amber, for v2 features
- .badge-v3 — gray, for v3 features

### Loading State
Class: .scopr-loading
- JetBrains Mono, text-base, #4ADE80, centred
- Format: // loading [thing]...

### Generating State
- Header: // preparing [thing]... in .scopr-loading style
- Cycling messages: framer-motion AnimatePresence, fade in/out, 3s interval
  Messages in JetBrains Mono, text-sm, rgba(188,202,187,0.6)
- Progress bar: animated sliding fill, track rgba(74,222,128,0.18),
  fill #4ADE80, infinite loop via framer-motion
- Reference: app/idea/[id]/launch/page.js generating phase

### Error States
Class: .scopr-error
- JetBrains Mono, text-xs, #ff6b6b
- Always start with ⚠
- Always include // try again → button (.btn-secondary) below

### Success States
Inline: .scopr-success-inline — JetBrains Mono, text-xs, #4ADE80
Banner: .scopr-success-banner
- green tinted card, green border
- Title: .scopr-success-banner-title (JetBrains Mono, text-sm, #4ADE80)
- Subtext: .scopr-success-banner-sub (text-sm, rgba(255,255,255,0.72))

